Hi bad_user,<p>I seen this on Twitter and just by scanning it quickly I learned some things, so that&#x27;s why I posted it here and thanks for sharing.<p>Can I ask about rule 5.2. SHOULD mutate state in actors only with &quot;context.become&quot;?<p>How would you use become to avoid using vars to keep state in an Actor like this?<p>class Account(var account: AccountDetails) extends Actor {
	def receive = {
		case msg: UpdateAccount => {
			account = msg.account
		}
	}
}
